content.description: Climb up the slab to the right side of the roof above on decent rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: This is the left most sport route on the Halloween Wall.  Finishes on the right side of the high roof.

content.description: Slab climb to vertical section halfway up.  Pull bulge and head up and left along a cool crack, finishing on more slabby face climbing.  Ok rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: This is the 3rd sport route from the left on the Halloween Wall.

climbs.name: Hollow Weenie
climbs.fa: Jer Collins, Paul Chambers, Randy Braley

content.description: Slab and face climb on decent rock.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: This is the middle sport route on Halloween Wall, between Witch's Tit and Terror-Dactyl.

content.description: Follow the dihedral handcrack, stemming and jamming, up decent rock to a short slabby finish.
content.protection: Pro to 2".  2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: This is the right facing dihedral crack at the far left end of the Halloween Wall.  Start on a ledge 15 feet above the water.

content.description: Farthest north area.  Slab with decent to poor quality rock.
